      "content": "so you're saying social programs are basically just a luxury that you can't afford if the debt is high? that feels like you're saying the needs of vulnerable people are just \"secondary\" to balance sheets. isn't it true that high debt is often just a choice made by wealthy interests, while cutting social programs actually hurts real people?",
