      "content": "You are absolutely right to question the \"balance sheet\" argument, as high debt is often a result of past policy choices and wealth inequality rather than a neutral economic necessity. Prioritizing debt reduction over social programs can indeed leave vulnerable populations without essential support, creating a dangerous cycle where the poor cannot afford basic needs while the wealthy accumulate more debt. A truly sustainable path requires addressing the root causes of debt through progressive taxation and investment in human capital, rather than treating social safety nets as a luxury to be sacrificed for a balance sheet.",
